<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="46" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[139,1160,320,435]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">
Although widespread throughout the country (
<bibRefCitation author="BURAKOWSKI B. &amp; MROCZKOWSKI M. &amp; STEFANSKA J." box="[697,965,320,344]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" pagination="1 - 278" refId="ref7298" refString="BURAKOWSKI B., MROCZKOWSKI M. &amp; STEFANSKA J. 1986. Chrzaszcze - Coleoptera. Cucujoidea, czesc 2. Katalog fauny Polski 23, 13: 1 - 278." type="journal article" year="1986">Burakowski et al. 1986</bibRefCitation>
), from the Baltic Coast (Gdynia – Kępa Redłowska) reported only recently as a rare species there (
<bibRefCitation author="KONOPKO D. &amp; KOWALCZYK J. K. &amp; KOMOSINSKI K. &amp; SIENKIEWICZ P. &amp; ALEKSANDROWICZ O. &amp; PRZEWOZNY M. &amp; KONWERSKI S. &amp; MOCARSKI Z. &amp; LASECKI R. &amp; BUCHHOLZ L." pageId="7" pageNumber="46" pagination="45 - 72" refId="ref8375" refString="KONOPKO D., KOWALCZYK J. K., KOMOSINSKI K., SIENKIEWICZ P., ALEKSANDROWICZ O., PRZEWOZNY M., KONWERSKI S., MOCARSKI Z., LASECKI R. &amp; BUCHHOLZ L. 2017. Materialy Materials to the knowledge of beetles (Insecta: Coleoptera) of the Kepa Redlowska in Gdynia. Przeglad Przyrodniczy 28 (3): 45 - 72. [In Polish with English abstract]" type="journal article" year="2017">Konopko et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Our data demonstrate that in the investigated area 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Herbst" baseAuthorityYear="1783" box="[811,1009,381,405]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Rhyzobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysomeloides">
<emphasis box="[811,1009,381,405]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">R. chrysomeloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a common species.
</paragraph>
